India's Ravindra Jadeja has been fined 50 per cent of his first Test match fee after his involvement in an incident with England bowler James Anderson at Trent Bridge.

The all-rounder was found guilty of 'conduct contrary to the spirit of the game' at an International Cricket Council (ICC) hearing on Friday.

Jadeja and Anderson clashed following the second day of the first Test in the five-match series on July 10.

